{"title": "Police Brutality Gambit", "content": "Officer O'Troper is in an interrogation room with Professor Evil, he's started getting somewhere. They found his fingerprints all over the Death Ray and they have a receipt for a fluxoid charger from Radio Shack paid for with foreign money out of Professor Evil's account. It's an open and shut- HEY! Why's the professor clawing at his own face? Prof. Evil then proceeds to cry Police Brutality and they're forced to release him, and he then finds an Ambulance Chaser and proceeds to unleash a Frivolous Lawsuit on poor old O'Troper. A subtrope of Wounded Gazelle Gambit which occurs in Police Procedurals. Basically a suspect injures himself and accuses the police of Police Brutality in order to try and get the charges dropped. Alternately, the suspect may incite the officer into hitting him.\n\nIn reality, this rarely works; real-life interrogations are sometimes filmed, while police cars normally have audio and video recorders running at all times. And both judges and juries are in general more disposed to believe the word of a cop when it comes down to a he-said, she-said situation (which can be unfortunate when the cop really is corrupt).\n\nNot to be confused with Good Cop/Bad Cop, where police use the threat of brutality as a gambit.\n\nSee also Arrested for Heroism. Not related to Suicide by Cop, where the individual concerned is trying to force a police officer to kill them.", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PoliceBrutalityGambit", "media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/MockTheWeek", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/CatsEye", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/GhostInTheShellStandAloneComplex", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/DirtyHarry", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TheInterview", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/HorribleBosses", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/Pyrokinesis", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/LesRipoux", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/HerculePoirot", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/AlasSmithAndJones", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/The